The article is a transcript of a press briefing by White House Press Secretary Jay Carney. Carney discusses various topics including President Obama's upcoming speech on long-term deficit reduction, the relationship between the speech and the debt ceiling vote, the budget deal, and the President's view on the House Republican budget plan. Carney also answers questions about General McChrystal's role in an advisory committee, the relationship between the CIA and ISI, and the President's position on Social Security and Medicare reform.